<!-- Changeling racial epic destiny -->

<RulesElement name="Doppleganger of Legend" type="Epic Destiny" internal-id="ID_HF_EPIC_DESTINY_1" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="10/12/2010 1:42:53 PM">
		<Prereqs> 21st level, changeling </Prereqs>
		<print-prereqs> 21st level, changeling </print-prereqs>
		<specific name="Class Features"> ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF4, ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF5, ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF6, ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF7 </specific>
		<specific name="Powers"> ID_FMP_HF_POWER_008 </specific>
		<specific name="_DisplayPowers"> ID_FMP_HF_POWER_008 </specific>
		<rules>
			<grant name="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF4" type="Class Feature" Level="21" />
			<grant name="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF5" type="Class Feature" Level="21" />
			<grant name="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF6" type="Class Feature" Level="24" />
			<grant name="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF7" type="Class Feature" Level="30" />
			<grant name="ID_FMP_HF_POWER_008" type="Power" Level="26" />
		</rules>
Changelings are viewed with distrust by many other races, both civilized and uncivilized. Their ability to change their forms is well-suited for all sorts of unsavory activities, and many who would abuse this ability if they had it fear changelings all the more. Tales have been borne from fevered imaginations of changelings with even greater abilities of shapechanging and infiltration. Changelings have called these stories "doppleganger tales" to keep from being associated with them. Dopplegangers can read thoughts, and assume any form. Dopplegangers are able to heal any wound by changing their forms to uninjured ones. Most people dismiss these tales as mere stories. But even some changelings would be surprised to learn that many of these tales are true.
The first changeling was said to be so skilled that she hid herself from the goddess who created her. Armed with this snippet and other ones like it, you sought to rediscover the secrets of form-changing lost for ages. 
The key, you found, was changing your form so completely that any concept of a "true form" became meaningless. Your form is you, and you are your form. With this seemingly simple realization, you took your first steps towards becoming a doppleganger of legend.
In time, your natural abilities became honed. You connected with your racial memories, providing you with knowledge of hundreds of languages beyond your own, and learned to open your mind to the thoughts of others.
Finally, your shapechanging reached its zenith. You can adapt to myriad environments and take the form of more exotic creatures.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Changeling Abilities" type="Class Feature" internal-id="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF4" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="7/2/2012 5:48:00 PM">
		<Category> 21 </Category>
		<Flavor> You enhance your native changeling abilities. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Increase your Charisma by 2, and your Intelligence or Dexerity by 2. </specific>
		<specific name="Level"> 21 </specific>
		<specific name="_CS_ShortDescription"> Increase Cha and Int or Dex by 2 </specific>
		<rules>
			<statadd name="Charisma" value="+2" />
			<select type="Class Feature" number="1" Category="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF4" />
		</rules>
You increase your Charisma by 2, and you increase your Dexterity or Intelligence by 2.
	</RulesElement>
