		<specific name="_SupportsID"> ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF4 </specific>
		<specific name="Short Description"> +2 to your Dexterity </specific>
		<specific name="_CS_ShortDescription"> +2 to your Dexterity </specific>
		<rules>
			<statadd name="Dexterity" value="+2" />
		</rules>
Add +2 to your Dexterity.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Changeling Cunning (Intelligence)" type="Class Feature" internal-id="ID_INTERNAL_CLASS_FEATURE_CHANGELING_CUNNING_(INTELLIGENCE)" source="HF Homebrew">
		<Category> ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF4 </Category>
		<specific name="_SupportsID"> ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF4 </specific>
		<specific name="Short Description"> +2 to your Intelligence </specific>
		<specific name="_CS_ShortDescription"> +2 to your Intelligence </specific>
		<rules>
			<statadd name="Intelligence" value="+2" />
		</rules>
Add +2 to your Intelligence.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Improved Changeling Disguise" type="Class Feature" internal-id="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF5" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="7/2/2012 5:48:00 PM">
		<Category> 21 </Category>
		<Flavor> Your changeling disguise extends beyond the superficial. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Changeling Disguise affects more. </specific>
		<specific name="Level"> 21 </specific>
		<specific name="_CS_ShortDescription"> Changeling disguise affects more </specific>
When you use your changeling disguise racial power, you may also change the appearance of your clothes, armor, and weapons. Your new form is considered your natural form in all ways, including for the purposes of truesight and using other polymorph effects. In addition, you do not age.
	</RulesElement>
<RulesElement name="Mastery of the Form" type="Class Feature" internal-id="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF6" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="7/2/2012 5:48:00 PM">
		<Category> 24 </Category>
		<Flavor> Your dedication to testing the limits of your shapechanging ability has brought even greater rewards. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Use another race's racial power, gain their senses, telepathy, and languages </specific>
		<specific name="Level"> 24 </specific>
		<specific name="_CS_ShortDescription"> Use another race's racial power, gain their senses, telepathy, and languages </specific>
While in an assumed form, you gain any special senses (such as low-light vision or darkvision) possessed by that form. Once per encounter, when you have assumed the form of another race, you may expend changeling trick to use an unleveled racial encounter power of that race. This requires that power's normal action.
You also gain telepathy 15, and you can speak and understand all languages.
	</RulesElement>
	<RulesElement name="Resculpt the Broken Flesh" type="Power" internal-id="ID_FMP_HF_POWER_008" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="10/12/2010 1:30:56 PM">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_UTILITY,ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_DAILY_USAGE,ID_HF_EPIC_DESTINY_1,ID_FMP_CATEGORY_9,ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_MINOR_ACTION,26 </Category>
		<Prereqs> Doppleganger of Legend </Prereqs>
		<Flavor> For a short time, you reach deep within yourself and use your native changeling abilities to heal your body. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Power Usage"> Daily </specific>
		<specific name="Display"> Doppleganger of Legend Utility 26 </specific>
		<specific name="Keywords"> Healing </specific>
		<specific name="Action Type"> Minor Action </specific>
		<specific name="Attack Type"> Personal  </specific>
		<specific name="Effect"> You gain regeneration 25 until the end of the encounter. </specific>
		<specific name="Special"> If you would die, you may expend this power or end its effects. You do not die, and instead regain hit points equal to your healing surge value.  </specific>
		<specific name="Class"> ID_HF_EPIC_DESTINY_1 </specific>
		<specific name="Level"> 26 </specific>
		<specific name="Power Type"> Utility </specific>
Your ability to change your form has grown well beyond that of normal changelings. Though it strains you, you can recover from nearly lethal injuries - and sometimes, even lethal ones.
	</RulesElement>
<RulesElement name="Greater Metamorphosis" type="Class Feature" internal-id="ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_HF7" source="HF Homebrew" revision-date="7/2/2012 5:48:00 PM">
		<Category> 30 </Category>
		<Flavor> In any form, your shapechanging ability gives you greater combat prowess than you would have thought possible. </Flavor>
		<specific name="Short Description"> Gain your choice of benefits while in an assumed form </specific>
		<specific name="Level"> 30 </specific>
		<specific name="_CS_ShortDescription"> Gain your choice of benefits while in an assumed form  </specific>
Your ability to change your form has reached its zenith. Whenever you use changeling disguise, you may choose to gain one of the following benefits. These benefits are not obvious to observers when not in use, allowing you to maintain a more mundane disguise as well.
* Aquatic - You gain the aquatic keyword, and a swim speed equal to your speed.
* Winged - You gain a fly speed equal to your speed.
* Armored - You gain a +2 bonus to all defenses.
* Resistant - You gain resist 20 against a specific damage type of your choice.</RulesElement>

